ummary    = Scrooge decides to take Louie to his Money Bin to show him the value of a hard day's work after witnessing his laziness. While there, Louie loses Scrooge's [[Number One Dime]] and decides to use [[Gyro Gearloose]]'s ([[Jim Rash]]) robotic light-bulb, [[Little Bulb]], to get it back. However, he causes it to become a giant coin-collecting robot, and is forced to stop him all on his own and retrieve the Dime before Scrooge notices. Meanwhile, Dewey and Webby face the McDuck Archives' dedicated keeper, [[Emily Quackfaster|Mrs. Quackfaster]] ([[Susanne Blakeslee]]), in order to gain information on Della and solve the mystery of her disappearance. In the end, they find a note from Della \u2013 \"Scrooge, I took ''The Spear of Selene,'' I'm sorry\" \u2013 and decide to keep this a secret until they know more. \n|LineColor        = FFEF00\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 4\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 4\n |Title           = The Beagle Birthday Massacre!\n |DirectedBy      = Dana Terrace\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Francisco Angones, Madison Bateman, Colleen Evanson, Christian Magalhaes & Bob Snow|t=Snow}}\n |Aux2            = Emmy Cicierega, Ben Holm & Jason Reicher\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2017|9|30}}\n |ProdCode        = 106\n |Viewers         = 0.38<ref>{{cite news|last1=Metcalf|first1=Mitch|title=SHOWBUZZDAILY's Top 150 Saturday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 9.30.2017|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-saturday-cable-originals-network-finals-9-30-2017.html|accessdate=October 4, 2017|work=ShowBuzz Daily|date=October 3, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180109010944/http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-saturday-cable-originals-network-finals-9-30-2017.html|archivedate=January 9, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = Disappointed after having to be left behind by the boys, Webby meets and bonds with a rebellious teen, Lena ([[Kimiko Glenn]]). The two inadvertently crash Ma Beagle's birthday party and are pursued by the whole Beagle clan. They and the boys, who were looking for Webby, are eventually captured, but they manage to escape and remain friends. Unbeknownst to the young ducks, Lena is revealed to be the niece of the evil sorceress, [[Magica De Spell]].\n|LineColor        = FFEF00\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 5\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 5\n |Title           = Terror of the Terra-firmians!\n |DirectedBy      = Matthew Humphreys & Tom Owens\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Francisco Angones, Madison Bateman, Colleen Evanson, Christian Magalhaes & Bob Snow|t=Magalhaes}}\n |Aux2            = David Baker, Owens, Vaughn Tada & Brandon Warren\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2017|10|7}}\n |ProdCode        = 110\n |Viewers         = 0.39<ref>Metcalf, Mitch (Oct 10, 2017) [http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-saturday-cable-originals-network-finals-10-7-2017.html UPDATED: SHOWBUZZDAILY's Top 150 Saturday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 10.7.2017] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180203174128/http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-saturday-cable-originals-network-finals-10-7-2017.html |date=February 3, 2018 }} Showbuzzdaily.</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = After seeing a scary movie, Huey, Webby, and Lena explore an abandoned subway line in search of legendary creatures, [[Land Beneath the Ground!|the Terra-firmians]], only to end up trapped underground with Mrs. Beakley, Louie, Dewey, and Launchpad. As they struggle to escape, Launchpad becomes more and more paranoid, leaving Dewey to help him come back to his senses. Huey and Webby argue over the creatures' existence, as the former believes only in his [[Junior Woodchucks|Junior Woodchuck]] Guidebook and is afraid to do anything that doesn't follow its instructions. In the end however, the two reconcile and find out that the Terra-firmians are actually real. In the midst of their adventure, Lena struggles to gain Mrs. Beakley's trust while secretly receiving instructions from Magica ([[Catherine Tate]]).  \n|LineColor        = FFEF00\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 6\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 6\n |Title           = The House of the Lucky Gander!\n |DirectedBy      = Matthew Humphreys & Tom Owens\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Francisco Angones, Madison Bateman, Colleen Evanson, Christian Magalhaes & Bob Snow|t=Magalhaes}}\n |Aux2            = Dalton E. Grant Jr., Vaughn Tada & Brandon Warren\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2017|10|14}}{{efn|name=oct14|On [[Disney XD (Canada)|Disney XD Canada]], the episodes \"The Infernal Internship of Mark Beaks!\" and \"The House of the Lucky Gander!\" aired in an inverted order, on October 14, 2017<ref>{{cite web|title=DISNEY XD CANADA October 14th listing|url=https://www.tvpassport.com/tv-listings/stations/disney-xd-canada/17172|website=TV Passport|publisher=TV Media Inc.|accessdate=16 October 2017|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20171014132743/https://www.tvpassport.com/tv-listings/stations/disney-xd-canada/17172|archivedate=October 14, 2017|date=14 October 2017|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref> and October 21, 2017<ref>{{cite web|title=DISNEY XD CANADA October 21st listing|url=https://www.tvpassport.com/tv-listings/stations/disney-xd-canada/17172|website=TV Passport|publisher=TV Media Inc.|accessdate=21 October 2017|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20171021195206/https://www.tvpassport.com/tv-listings/stations/disney-xd-canada/17172|archivedate=October 21, 2017|date=21 October 2017|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref> respectively.}}\n |ProdCode        = 107\n |Viewers         = 0.34<ref>Metcalf, Mitch (Oct 17, 2017) [http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-saturday-cable-originals-network-finals-10-14-2017.html UPDATED: SHOWBUZZDAILY's Top 150 Saturday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 10.14.2017] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171017201758/http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-saturday-cable-originals-network-finals-10-14-2017.html |date=October 17, 2017 }} Showbuzzdaily.</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = During their search for The Temple of the Golden Cricket, Scrooge, the nephews, Webby, and Donald make a stop at a casino resort in [[Macau|Macaw]] to meet with Donald's cousin, [[Gladstone Gander]] ([[Paul F. Tompkins]]). Louie starts hanging out with Gladstone, resulting in Donald competing for his nephew's attention. Meanwhile, Scrooge and the rest of the kids try to find the exit, but the owner of the casino, [[Liu Haichan|Toad Liu Hai]] ([[BD Wong]]), keeps distracting the kids with different gifts. They eventually learn that Liu Hai is actually a luck vampire that had been holding Gladstone hostage to harvest his good luck. Following a competition to decide everyone's fates, the family manages to beat the vampire and free Gladstone, all while Louie reconciles with Donald.\n|LineColor        = FFEF00\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 7\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 7\n |Title           = The Infernal Internship of Mark Beaks!\n |DirectedBy      = John Aoshima\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Francisco Angones, Madison Bateman, Colleen Evanson, Christian Magalhaes & Bob Snow|t=Evanson}}\n |Aux2            = Mark Garcia, Matthew Humphreys & Tanner Johnson\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2017|10|21}}{{efn|name=oct14}}\n |ProdCode        = 108\n |Viewers         = 0.32<ref>Metcalf, Mitch (Oct 24, 2017) [http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-saturday-cable-originals-network-finals-10-21-2017.html UPDATED: SHOWBUZZDAILY's Top 150 Saturday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 10.21.2017] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171024205833/http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-saturday-cable-originals-network-finals-10-21-2017.html |date=October 24, 2017 }} Showbuzzdaily.</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = Huey and Dewey compete to get a coveted internship under Duckburg's tech mogul and up-and-coming billionaire, Mark Beaks ([[Josh Brener]]). Just then, industrial spy Falcon Graves ([[Robin Atkin Downes]]) arrives to take Beaks' Project Ta-Dah, only to learn it's nothing and it was Beaks who hired him so he could build hype for a fake product and become a billionaire. Angered by this, Graves attempts to kill Beaks, but Huey and Dewey manage to put aside their differences in order to save him. Meanwhile, Scrooge reluctantly teams up with Glomgold to get rid of Beaks, but he quickly grows tired of the overly-complicated scheme and walks out on him. \n|LineColor        = FFEF00\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 8\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 8\n |Title           = The Living Mummies of Toth-Ra!\n |DirectedBy      = Dana Terrace\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Francisco Angones, Madison Bateman, Colleen Evanson, Christian Magalhaes & Bob Snow|t=Bateman}}\n |Aux2            = Emmy Cicierega, Ben Holm & Jason Reicher\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2017|10|28}}\n |ProdCode        = 109\n |Viewers         = 0.29<ref>Metcalf, Mitch (Oct 31, 2017) [http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-saturday-cable-originals-network-finals-10-28-2017.html UPDATED: SHOWBUZZDAILY's Top 150 Saturday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 10.28.2017] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171107030715/http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-saturday-cable-originals-network-finals-10-28-2017.html |date=November 7, 2017 }} Showbuzzdaily.</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = Scrooge, the boys, Webby, and Launchpad enter an Egyptian pyramid in search of the lost tomb of the mummified pharaoh, Toth-Ra ([[Bassem Youssef]]), but become separated. Louie and Webby are imprisoned by Toth-Ra himself while the rest of the group try to gain the support of his servants, led by Amunet ([[Cree Summer]]).\n|LineColor        = FFEF00\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 9\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 9\n |Title           = The Impossible Summit of Mt. Neverrest!\n |DirectedBy      = Tom Owens & Matt Youngberg\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Francisco Angones, Madison Bateman, Colleen Evanson, Christian Magalhaes, Bob Snow, Noelle Stevenson & Matt Youngberg|t=Angones & Stevenson}}\n |Aux2            =  Mark Garcia, Dalton E. Grant Jr., Kalvin Lee & Calvin Suggs\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2017|12|2}}\n |ProdCode        = 104\n |Viewers         = 0.40<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-saturday-cable-originals-network-finals-12-2-2017.html|title=UPDATED:  SHOWBUZZDAILY's Top 150 Saturday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 12.2.2017 \u2013 Showbuzz Daily|author=|date=|website=www.showbuzzdaily.com|accessdate=February 6, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171207083129/http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-saturday-cable-originals-network-finals-12-2-2017.html|archivedate=December 7, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = Scrooge, the nephews, Webby, and Launchpad spend their Christmas attempting to climb the \"unclimbable\" Mt. Neverrest, a task Scrooge failed at seventy-five years earlier due to his treacherous guide George Mallardy. Launchpad is convinced by a salesman ([[Carlos Alazraqui]]) that he's dying of \"ice-fever\", Webby and Dewey try to accomplish the perfect sledding experience, Huey attempts to discover Neverrest's secret: [[wormhole]]s, and Louie, figuring out that Launchpad was obviously conned, pulls off his own scam to trick the salesman to confess the truth to the townspeople and expose him as a fraud.\n|LineColor        = FFEF00\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 10\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 10\n |Title           = The Spear of Selene!\n |DirectedBy      = Dana Terrace\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Francisco Angones, Madison Bateman, Colleen Evanson, Christian Magalhaes & Bob Snow|t=Bateman}}\n |Aux2            = Emmy Cicierega, Ben Holm & Jason Reicher\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|5|4}}{{efn|Beginning with this episode, new episodes of the show premiere on Disney Channel instead of Disney XD.}}\n |ProdCode        = 112\n |Viewers         = 1.09<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-friday-cable-originals-network-finals-5-4-2018.html|title=SHOWBUZZDAILY's Top 150 Friday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 5.4.2018 \u2013 Showbuzz Daily|author=Mitch Metcalf|date=May 7, 2018|website=www.showbuzzdaily.com|accessdate=May 7, 2018}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = Scrooge and his family are stuck on the Island of Ithaquack, home of the [[Greek gods]], where Dewey and Webby try to search for ''The Spear of Selene'' and uncover the mystery of Della's disappearance. However, Dewey struggles with the possibility that his mother may not have been a good person. They later find out that ''The Spear of Selene'' does not belong to [[Selene]] ([[Nia Vardalos]]), goddess of the Moon, who reveals that Della was a great person and friend. Meanwhile, Donald is dragged into a competition to settle a dispute between Scrooge and [[Zeus]] ([[Michael Chiklis]]). [[Hercules|Storkules]] ([[Chris Diamantopoulos]]), Zeus' son and an acquaintance of Donald's, encourages him to continue adventuring, even in spite of Della's disappearance. \n |LineColor       = FFEF00\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 11\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 11\n |Title           = Beware the B.U.D.D.Y. System!\n |DirectedBy      = John Aoshima\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Francisco Angones, Madison Bateman, Colleen Evanson, Christian Magalhaes & Bob Snow|t=Angones}}\n |Aux2            = Benjamin Balistreri, Evon Freeman, Mark Garcia, Tanner Johnson & John Ramirez\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|5|11}}\n |ProdCode        = 114\n |Viewers         = 0.68<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-friday-cable-originals-network-finals-5-11-2018.html|title=SHOWBUZZDAILY's 