ame, [[List of DuckTales characters#Goldie O'Gilt|Goldie O'Gilt]] ([[Allison Janney]]), and they team up to find the Golden Lagoon of White Agony Plains. They succeed, but Glomgold intervenes, seemingly causing Goldie's death and gaining the gold. As Glomgold prepares to get rid of Scrooge, Goldie reappears alive, saves him, and escapes with the gold. Upon returning home, Scrooge finds Goldie's note saying if he ever wants any more gold in his life, he should come find her.\n |LineColor       = FFEF00\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 16\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 16\n |Title           = Day of the Only Child!\n |DirectedBy      = Tanner Johnson & Dana Terrace\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Francisco Angones, Madison Bateman, Colleen Evanson, Christian Magalhaes & Bob Snow|t=Snow}}\n |Aux2            = Emmy Cicierega, Ben Holm & Jason Reicher\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|6|30}}\n |ProdCode        = 115\n |Viewers         = 0.78<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-saturday-cable-originals-network-finals-6-30-2018.html|title=Top 150 Saturday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 6.30.2018|work=Showbuzz Daily|author=Mitch Metcalf|date=July 2, 2018|access-date=July 2, 2018}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = On \"Only Child Day\", a holiday that Dewey made up, the nephews split up and spend the day pretending to be only children. Huey teaches Burger and Bouncer Beagle how to be good Junior Woodchucks, Louie attempts to befriend spoiled, insane child billionaire [[List of DuckTales characters#Doofus Drake|Doofus Drake]] ([[John Gemberling]]), and Dewey records an episode of his own late-night talk show, \"Dewey Dew-Night\"; all while Webby attempts to keep them all together.\n |LineColor       = FFEF00\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 17\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 17\n |Title           = From the Confidential Case Files of Agent 22!\n |DirectedBy      = Tanner Johnson\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Francisco A