ports Club]]. The ground was used during the [[2005 Women's Cricket World Cup]] and for a single other women's ODI. in 2007 during which the only five-wicket haul on the ground was taken.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/23/1647.html Harlequins Sports Club, Pretoria], CricketArchive. Retrieved 2020-03-07. {{subscription}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ Five-wicket hauls in Women's One Day Internationals at Harlequins\n|-\n! No.\n! Bowler\n! Date\n! Team\n! Opposing Team\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:20px;\"|Inn\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:20px;\"|O\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:20px;\"|R\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:20px;\"|W\n! Result\n|-\n| 1 || [[Urooj Mumtaz]] || {{dts|format=dmy|2007|1|22}} || {{crw|PAK}} || {{crw|SA}} || 1 || 6.5 || 40 || 5 || South Africa won<ref>[https://www.espncricinfo.com/series/14462/game/271465/south-africa-women-vs-pakistan-women-2nd-odi-pakistan-women-tour-of-south-africa-2006-07 2nd ODI, Pakistan Women tour of South Africa at Pretoria, Jan 22 2007], [[CricInfo]]. Retrieved 2020-03-07.</ref>\n|}\n\n==Kingsmead, Durban==\n{{main|List of international cricket five-wicket hauls at Kingsmead}}\n\n==Lord's No. 1 Ground, Durban==\nNine five-wicket hauls were taken in Test matches at [[Lord's No. 1 Ground]] in the four Test matches played on the ground. The ground no longer exists.<ref>[https://www.espncricinfo.com/ci/content/ground/59090.html Lord's], [[CricInfo]]. Retrieved 2020-03-07.</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+ Five-wicket hauls in Men's Test matches at Lord's Number 1 Ground\n|- \n! No.\n! Bowler\n! Date\n! Team\n! Opposing Team\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:20px;\"|Inn\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:20px;\"|O\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:20px;\"|R\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:20px;\"|W\n! Result\n|-\n|-\n| 1 || [[Bert Vogler]] || {{dts|format=dmy|1910|1|21}} || [[South Africa national cricket team|South Africa]]{{efn|The British colonies in South Africa did not use a common flag until 1910 when the [[Union of South Africa]] was created and the [[South Africa Red Ensign]] was used as the de-facto flag for the colony.<ref name=apb>Burgers AP (2008) ''The South African flag book: the history of South African flags from Dias to Mandela'', pp.152\u2013153. Pretoria: Protea Boekhuis. {{isbn|1869191129}}</ref>}} || {{cr|ENG}} || 2 || 30 || 83 || 5 || South Africa won<ref name=l1910>[https://www.espncricinfo.com/series/17642/game/62502/south-africa-vs-england-2nd-test-england-tour-of-south-africa-1909-10 2nd Test, England tour of South Africa at Durban, Jan 21-26 1910], [[CricInfo]]. Retrieved 2020-03-07.</ref>\n|- \n| 2 || [[Aubrey Faulkner]] || {{dts|format=dmy|1910|1|21}} || [[South Africa national cricket team|South Africa]] || {{cr|ENG}} || 4 || 33.4 || 87 || 6 || South Africa won<ref name=l1910/>\n|- \n| 3 || [[Sydney Barnes]]{{efn-ua|name=sb|Barnes took two five-wicket hauls in both of the matches on the ground in 1913 and 1914.}} || {{dts|format=dmy|1913|12|13}} || {{cr|ENG}} || {{cr|RSA|1912}} || 1 || 19.4 || 57 || 5 || England won<ref name=l1913>[https://www.espncricinfo.com/series/17629/game/62516/south-africa-vs-england-1st-test-england-tour-of-south-africa-1913-14 1st Test, England tour of South Africa at Durban, Dec 13-17 1913], [[CricInfo]]. Retrieved 2020-03-07.</ref>\n|- \n| 4 || [[Sydney Barnes]]{{efn-ua|name=sb}} || {{dts|format=dmy|1913|12|13}} || {{cr|ENG}} || {{cr|RSA|1912}} || 3 || 25 || 48 || 5 || England won<ref name=l1913/>\n|- \n| 5 || [[Sydney Barnes]]{{efn-ua|name=sb}} || {{dts|format=dmy|1914|2|14}} || {{cr|ENG}} || {{cr|RSA|1912}} || 1 || 29.5 || 56 || 7 || Drawn<ref name=l1914>[https://www.espncricinfo.com/series/17629/game/62519/south-africa-vs-england-4th-test-england-tour-of-south-africa-1913-14 4th Test, England tour of South Africa at Durban, Feb 14-18 1914], [[CricInfo]]. Retrieved 2020-03-07.</ref>\n|- \n| 6 || [[Claude Carter]] || {{dts|format=dmy|1914|2|14}} || {{cr|RSA|1912}} || {{cr|ENG}} || 2 || 28 || 50 || 6 || 