 Jones|Iggy Jones]] Man of the Match trophy was first awarded in 1993\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:lightblue;\" | '''Year'''\n! style=\"background:gold;\" | '''Winner'''\n! style=\"background:gold;\" | Score\n! style=\"background:silver;\"| Score\n! style=\"background:silver;\" | '''Opponent'''\n!! style=\"background:lightblue;\" |Venue\n! style=\"background:lightblue;\" |Match<br>Report\n! style=\"background:lightblue;\" |Winning<br>Captain\n! style=\"background:lightblue;\" |Man Of The Match<br>(Iggy Jones)\n|-\n| align=center | 2020\n| align=center | \n| align=center | \n| align=center | \n| align=center | \n| align=center | [[Athletic Grounds|Armagh]]\n| align=center | \n| align=center | \n| align=center | \n|-\n| align=center | 2019\n| align=center | '''[[St. Michael's College (Enniskillen)|St. Michael's College, Enniskillen]]<sup>(7)</sup>'''\n| align=center | 0-16\n| align=center | 2-06\n| align=center | [[Christian Brothers Grammar School, Omagh|Omagh CBS]]\n| align=center | [[Athletic Grounds|Armagh]]\n| align=center | <ref>https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/gaelic-games/47609833</ref>\n| align=center | Brandon Horan\n| align=center | Darragh McBrien<br>St. Michael's College\n|-\n| align=center | 2018\n| align=center | '''St. Ronan's College, Lurgan <sup></sup>'''\n| align=center | 1-09\n| align=center | 1-07\n| align=center | [[St Mary's Grammar School|St. Mary's Grammar School, Magherafelt]]\n| align=center | [[Athletic Grounds|Armagh]]\n| align=center | <ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.irishexaminer.com/sport/gaa/ronans-make-history-with-first-title-triumph-468524.html |title=Ronan\u2019s make history with first title triumph |accessdate=20 March 2018 |work=[[Irish Examiner]] |publisher= |date= 20 March 2018}}</ref>\n| align=center | Jamie Haughey\n| align=center | Rioghan Meehan<br>St. Ronan's College\n|-\n| align=center |  2017\n| align=center | [[St Mary's Grammar School|St. Mary's Grammar School, Magherafelt]]<sup></sup>\n| align=cent